707219f-a.text:
Village Road North, south side, opposite Lake Street, showing the house occupied by J.S. Van Cleet in 18737 which is still standing in 1929, and to the left of which, partially seen, is Ho. 28; in the background, is a section
of P.S. No. 95.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

707094f-a.folder: Ave. U & Lake St., Brooklyn, NY

707095f-a.text:
Ave. U, south side, west from Lake Street. Also seen is Lake Street, east side, in the foreground, between Village Road north, and Ave. U. At the extreme left, shows a section of Public School No. 95.
April 21, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
